modules.description: Parses and prints semantic version strings according to Semver 2.0.0 specifications, handling major, minor, patch, and pre-release identifiers. Works with strings and a custom version type that encapsulates numeric and alphanumeric components. Used to validate version strings from configuration files and generate standardized output for package metadata.

Parses and constructs semantic versions from strings or component parts, comparing them according to 2.0.0 specifications. Works with integers for major, minor, and patch versions, along with optional pre-release and build metadata. Used to validate version strings, determine precedence between releases, and generate human-readable representations.
